## Write a program to check alphabet

Check that the given character is an alphabet or not (a-z, A-Z).

```
Input  : a
Output : Alphabet
```

---

<CodeBlock slug="check-alphabet" >

```c
//CheckAlphabet.c

#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    char ch;
    scanf("%c",&ch);
    if((ch>='A' && ch<='Z') || (ch>='a' && ch<='z')) printf("Alphabet\n");
    else printf("Not Alphabet\n");
    return 0;
}
```

